ent "LINE" [PCDATA "First, good Peter Quince, say what the play treats"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "on, then read the names of the actors, and so grow"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "to a point."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Marry, our play is, The most lamentable comedy, and"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "most cruel death of Pyramus and Thisby."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A very good piece of work, I assure you, and a"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "merry. Now, good Peter Quince, call forth your"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "actors by the scroll. Masters, spread yourselves."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Answer as I call you. Nick Bottom, the weaver."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ready. Name what part I am for, and proceed."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You, Nick Bottom, are set down for Pyramus."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What is Pyramus? a lover, or a tyrant?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A lover, that kills himself most gallant for love."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That will ask some tears in the true performing of"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "it: if I do it, let the audience look to their"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "eyes; I will move storms, I will condole in some"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "measure. To the rest: yet my chief humour is for a"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "tyrant: I could play Ercles rarely, or a part to"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "tear a cat in, to make all split."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The raging rocks"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And shivering shocks"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Shall break the locks"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Of prison gates;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And Phib