r Quince."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Robin Starveling, you must play Thisby's mother."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Tom Snout, the tinker."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "SNOUT"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Here, Peter Quince."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You, Pyramus' father: myself, Thisby's father:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Snug, the joiner; you, the lion's part: and, I"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "hope, here is a play fitted."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "SNUG"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Have you the lion's part written? pray you, if it"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "be, give it me, for I am slow of study."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You may do it extempore, for it is nothing but roaring."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Let me play the lion too: I will roar, that I will"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "do any man's heart good to hear me; I will roar,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "that I will make the duke say 'Let him roar again,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "let him roar again.'"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "An you should do it too terribly, you would fright"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "the duchess and the ladies, that they would shriek;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "and that were enough to hang us all."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "ALL"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That would hang us, every mother's son."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I grant you, friends, if that you should fright the"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "ladies out of their wits, they would have no more"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "discretion but to hang us: but I will aggravate my"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "voice so that I will roar you as gently as any"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "sucking dove; I will roar you an 'twere any"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "nightingale."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You can play no part but Pyramus; for Pyramus is a"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "sweet-faced man; a proper man, as one shall see in a"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "summer's day; a most lovely gentleman-like man:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "therefore you must needs play Pyramus."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Well, I will undertake it. What beard were I best"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "to play it in?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Why, what you will."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I will discharge it in either your straw-colour"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "beard, your orange-tawny beard, your purple-in-grain"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "beard, or your French-crown-colour beard, your"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "perfect yellow."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Some of your French crowns have no hair at all, and"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "then you will play bare-faced. But, masters, here"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "are your parts: and I am to entreat you, request"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "you and desire you, to con them by to-morrow night;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "and meet me in the palace wood, a mile without the"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "town, by moonlight; there will we rehearse, for if"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "we meet in the city, we shall be dogged with"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "company, and our devices known. In the meantime I"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "will draw a bill of properties, such as our play"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "wants. I pray you, fail me not."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We will meet; and there we may rehearse most"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "obscenely and courageously. Take pains; be perfect: adieu."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "At the duke's oak we meet."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Enough; hold or cut bow-strings."]]]],Element "ACT" [Element "TITLE" [PCDATA "ACT II"],Element "SCENE" [Element "TITLE" [PCDATA "SCENE I.  A wood near Athens."],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "How now, spirit! whither wander you?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Fairy"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Over hill, over dale,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thorough bush, thorough brier,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Over park, over pale,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thorough flood, thorough fire,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I do wander everywhere,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Swifter than the moon's sphere;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And I serve the fairy queen,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To dew her orbs upon the green."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The cowslips tall her pensioners be:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In their gold coats spots you see;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Those be rubies, fairy favours,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In those freckles live their savours:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I must go seek some dewdrops here"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And hang a pearl in every cowslip's ear."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Farewell, thou lob of spirits; I'll be gone:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Our queen and all our elves come here anon."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The king doth keep his revels here to-night:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Take heed the queen come not within his sight;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For Oberon is passing fell and wrath,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Because that she as her attendant hath"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A lovely boy, stolen from an Indian king;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "She never had so sweet a changeling;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And jealous Oberon would have the child"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Knight of his train, to trace the forests wild;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But she perforce withholds the loved boy,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Crowns him with flowers and makes him all her joy:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And now they never meet in grove or green,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "By fountain clear, or spangled starlight sheen,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But, they do square, that all their elves for fear"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Creep into acorn-cups and hide them there."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Fairy"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Either I mistake your shape and making quite,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Or else you are that shrewd and knavish sprite"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Call'd Robin Goodfellow: are not you he"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That frights the maidens of the villagery;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Skim milk, and sometimes labour in the quern"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And bootless make the breathless housewife churn;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And sometime make the drink to bear no barm;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Mislead night-wanderers, laughing at their harm?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Those that Hobgoblin call you and sweet Puck,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You do their work, and they shall have good luck:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Are not you he?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thou speak'st aright;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I am that merry wanderer of the night."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I jest to Oberon and make him smile"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When I a fat and bean-fed horse beguile,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Neighing in likeness of a filly foal:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And sometime lurk I in a gossip's bowl,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In very likeness of a roasted crab,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And when she drinks, against her lips I bob"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And on her wither'd dewlap pour the ale."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The wisest aunt, telling the saddest tale,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Sometime for three-foot stool mistaketh me;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Then slip I from her bum, down topples she,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And 'tailor' cries, and falls into a cough;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And then the whole quire hold their hips and laugh,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And waxen in their mirth and neeze and swear"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A merrier hour was never wasted there."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But, room, fairy! here comes Oberon."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Fairy"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And here my mistress. Would that he were gone!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ill met by moonlight, proud Titania."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What, jealous Oberon! Fairies, skip hence:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I have forsworn his bed and company."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Tarry, rash wanton: am not I thy lord?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Then I must be thy lady: but I know"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When thou hast stolen away from fairy land,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And in the shape of Corin sat all day,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Playing on pipes of corn and versing love"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To amorous Phillida. Why art thou here,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come from the farthest Steppe of India?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But that, forsooth, the bouncing Amazon,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Your buskin'd mistress and your warrior love,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To Theseus must be wedded, and you come"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To give their bed joy and prosperity."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "How canst thou thus for shame, Titania,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Glance at my credit with Hippolyta,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Knowing I know thy love to Theseus?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Didst thou not lead him through the glimmering night"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "From Perigenia, whom he ravished?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And make him with fair AEgle break his faith,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With Ariadne and Antiopa?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "These are the forgeries of jealousy:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And never, since the middle summer's spring,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Met we on hill, in dale, forest or mead,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "By paved fountain or by rushy brook,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Or in the beached margent of the sea,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To dance our ringlets to the whistling wind,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But with thy brawls thou hast disturb'd our sport."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Therefore the winds, piping to us in vain,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "As in revenge, have suck'd up from the sea"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Contagious fogs; which falling in the land"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Have every pelting river made so proud"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That they have overborne their continents:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The ox hath therefore stretch'd his yoke in vain,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The ploughman lost his sweat, and the green corn"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hath rotted ere his youth attain'd a beard;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The fold stands empty in the drowned field,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And crows are fatted with the murrion flock;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The nine men's morris is fill'd up with mud,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And the quaint mazes in the wanton green"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For lack of tread are undistinguishable:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The human mortals want their winter here;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No night is now with hymn or carol blest:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Therefore the moon, the governess of floods,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Pale in her anger, washes all the air,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That rheumatic diseases do abound:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And thorough this distemperature we see"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The seasons alter: hoary-headed frosts"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Far in the fresh lap of the crimson rose,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And on old Hiems' thin and icy crown"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "An odorous chaplet of sweet summer buds"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Is, as in mockery, set: the spring, the summer,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The childing autumn, angry winter, change"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Their wonted liveries, and the mazed world,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "By their increase, now knows not which is which:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And this same progeny of evils comes"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "From our debate, from our dissension;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We are their parents and original."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Do you amend it then; it lies in you:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Why should Titania cross her Oberon?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I do but beg a little changeling boy,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To be my henchman."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Set your heart at rest:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The fairy land buys not the child of me."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "His mother was a votaress of my order:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And, in the spiced Indian air, by night,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Full often hath she gossip'd by my side,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And sat with me on Neptune's yellow sands,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Marking the embarked traders on the flood,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When we have laugh'd to see the sails conceive"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And grow big-bellied with the wanton wind;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Which she, with pretty and with swimming gait"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Following,--her womb then rich with my young squire,--"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Would imitate, and sail upon the land,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To fetch me trifles, and return again,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "As from a voyage, rich with merchandise."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But she, being mortal, of that boy did die;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And for her sake do I rear up her boy,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And for her sake I will not part with him."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "How long within this wood intend you stay?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Perchance till after Theseus' wedding-day."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If you will patiently dance in our round"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And see our moonlight revels, go with us;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If not, shun me, and I will spare your haunts."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Give me that boy, and I will go with thee."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Not for thy fairy kingdom. Fairies, away!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We shall chide downright, if I longer stay."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Well, go thy way: thou shalt not from this grove"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Till I torment thee for this injury."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My gentle Puck, come hither. Thou rememberest"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Since once I sat upon a promontory,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And heard a mermaid on a dolphin's back"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Uttering such dulcet and harmonious breath"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That the rude sea grew civil at her song"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And certain stars shot madly from their spheres,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To hear the sea-maid's music."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I remember."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That very time I saw, but t