d ere I take this charm from off her sight,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "As I can take it with another herb,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I'll make her render up her page to me."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But who comes here? I am invisible;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And I will overhear their conference."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I love thee not, therefore pursue me not."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Where is Lysander and fair Hermia?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The one I'll slay, the other slayeth me."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thou told'st me they were stolen unto this wood;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And here am I, and wode within this wood,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Because I cannot meet my Hermia."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hence, get thee gone, and follow me no more."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You draw me, you hard-hearted adamant;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But yet you draw not iron, for my heart"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Is true as steel: leave you your power to draw,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And I shall have no power to follow you."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Do I entice you? do I speak you fair?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Or, rather, do I not in plainest truth"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Tell you, I do not, nor I cannot love you?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And even for that do I love you the more."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I am your spaniel; and, Demetrius,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The more you beat me, I will fawn on you:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Use me but as your spaniel, spurn me, strike me,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Neglect me, lose me; only give me leave,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Unworthy as I am, to follow you."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What worser place can I beg in your love,--"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And yet a place of high respect with me,--"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Than to be used as you use your dog?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Tempt not too much the hatred of my spirit;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For I am sick when I do look on thee."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And I am sick when I look not on you."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You do impeach your modesty too much,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To leave the city and commit yourself"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Into the hands of one that loves you not;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To trust the opportunity of night"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And the ill counsel of a desert place"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With the rich worth of your virginity."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Your virtue is my privilege: for that"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "It is not night when I do see your face,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Therefore I think I am not in the night;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Nor doth this wood lack worlds of company,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For you in my respect are all the world:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Then how can it be said I am alone,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When all the world is here to look on me?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I'll run from thee and hide me in the brakes,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And leave thee to the mercy of wild beasts."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The wildest hath not such a heart as you."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Run when you will, the story shall be changed:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Apollo flies, and Daphne holds the chase;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The dove pursues the griffin; the mild hind"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Makes speed to catch the tiger; bootless speed,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When cowardice pursues and valour flies."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I will not stay thy questions; let me go:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Or, if thou follow me, do not believe"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But I shall do thee mischief in the wood."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ay, in the temple, in the town, the field,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You do me mischief. Fie, Demetrius!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Your wrongs do set a scandal on my sex:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We cannot fight for love, as men may do;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We should be wood and were not made to woo."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I'll follow thee and make a heaven of hell,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To die upon the hand I love so well."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Fare thee well, nymph: ere he do leave this grove,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thou shalt fly him and he shall seek thy love."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hast thou the flower there? Welcome, wanderer."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ay, there it is."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I pray thee, give it me."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I know a bank where the wild thyme blows,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Where oxlips and the nodding violet grows,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Quite over-canopied with luscious woodbine,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With sweet musk-roses and with eglantine:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "There sleeps Titania sometime of the night,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lull'd in these flowers with dances and delight;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And there the snake throws her enamell'd skin,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Weed wide enough to wrap a fairy in:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And with the juice of this I'll streak her eyes,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And make her full of hateful fantasies."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Take thou some of it, and seek through this grove:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A sweet Athenian lady is in love"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With a disdainful youth: anoint his eyes;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But do it when the next thing he espies"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "May be the lady: thou shalt know the man"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "By the Athenian garments he hath on."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Effect it with some care, that he may prove"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "More fond on her than she upon her love:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And look thou meet me ere the first cock crow."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Fear not, my lord, your servant shall do so."]]],Element "SCENE" [Element "TITLE" [PCDATA "SCENE II.  Another part of the wood."],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come, now a roundel and a fairy song;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Then, for the third part of a minute, hence;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Some to kill cankers in the musk-rose buds,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Some war with rere-mice for their leathern wings,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To make my small elves coats, and some keep back"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The clamorous owl that nightly hoots and wonders"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "At our quaint spirits. Sing me now asleep;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Then to your offices and let me rest."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You spotted snakes with double tongue,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thorny hedgehogs, be not seen;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Newts and blind-worms, do no wrong,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come not near our fairy queen."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Philomel, with melody"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Sing in our sweet lullaby;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lulla, lulla, lullaby, lulla, lulla, lullaby:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Never harm,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Nor spell nor charm,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come our lovely lady nigh;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So, good night, with lullaby."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Weaving spiders, come not here;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hence, you long-legg'd spinners, hence!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Beetles black, approach not near;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Worm nor snail, do no offence."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Philomel, with melody, &amp;c."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Fairy"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hence, away! now all is well:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "One aloof stand sentinel."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What thou seest when thou dost wake,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Do it for thy true-love take,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Love and languish for his sake:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Be it ounce, or cat, or bear,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Pard, or boar with bristled hair,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In thy eye that shall appear"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When thou wakest, it is thy dear:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Wake when some vile thing is near."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Fair love, you faint with wandering in the wood;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And to speak troth, I have forgot our way:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We'll rest us, Hermia, if you think it good,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And tarry for the comfort of the day."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Be it so, Lysander: find you out a bed;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For I upon this bank will rest my head."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "One turf shall serve as pillow for us both;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "One heart, one bed, two bosoms and one troth."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Nay, good Lysander; for my sake, my dear,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lie further off yet, do not lie so near."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O, take the sense, sweet, of my innocence!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Love takes the meaning in love's conference."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I mean, that my heart unto yours is knit"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So that but one heart we can make of it;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Two bosoms interchained with an oath;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So then two bosoms and a single troth."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Then by your side no bed-room me deny;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For lying so, Hermia, I do not lie."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lysander riddles very prettily:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now much beshrew my manners and my pride,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If Hermia meant to say Lysander lied."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But, gentle friend, for love and courtesy"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lie further off; in human modesty,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Such separation as may well be said"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Becomes a virtuous bachelor and a maid,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So far be distant; and, good night, sweet friend:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thy love ne'er alter till thy sweet life end!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Amen, amen, to that fair prayer, say I;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And then end life when I end loyalty!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Here is my bed: sleep give thee all his rest!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With half that wish the wisher's eyes be press'd!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Through the forest have I gone."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But Athenian found I none,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "On whose eyes I might approve"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This flower's force in stirring love."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Night and silence.--Who is here?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Weeds of Athens he doth wear:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This is he, my master said,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Despised the Athenian maid;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And here the maiden, sleeping sound,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "On the dank and dirty ground."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Pretty soul! she durst not lie"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Near this lack-love, this kill-courtesy."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Churl, upon thy eyes I throw"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "All the power this charm doth owe."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When thou wakest, let love forbid"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Sleep his seat on thy eyelid:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So awake when I am gone;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For I must now to Oberon."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Stay, though thou kill me, sweet Demetrius."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I charge thee, hence, and do not haunt me thus."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O, wilt thou darkling leave me? do not so."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Stay, on thy peril: I alone will go."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O, I am out of breath in this fond chase!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The more my prayer, the lesser is my grace."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Happy is Hermia, wheresoe'er she lies;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For she hath blessed and attractive eyes."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "How came her eyes so bright? Not with salt tears:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If so, my eyes are oftener wash'd than hers."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No, no, I am as ugly as a bear;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For beasts that meet me run away for fear:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Therefore no marvel though Demetrius"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Do, as a monster fly my presence thus."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What wicked and dissembling glass of mine"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Made me compare with Hermia's sphery eyne?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But who is here? Lysander! on the ground!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Dead? or asleep? I see no blood, no wound."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lysander if you live, good sir, awake."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And run through fire I will for thy sweet sake."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Transparent Helena! Nature shows art,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That through thy bosom makes me see thy heart."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Where is Demetrius? O, how fit a word"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Is that vile name to perish on my sword!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Do not say so, Lysander; say not so"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What though he love your Hermia? Lord, what though?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Yet Hermia still loves you: then be content."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Content with Hermia! No; I do repent"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The tedious minutes I with her have spent."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Not Hermia but Helena I love:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Who will not change a raven for a dove?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The will of man is by his reason sway'd;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And reason says you are the worthier maid."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Things growing are not ripe until their season"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So I, being young, till now ripe not to reason;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And touching now the point of human skill,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Reason becomes the marshal to my will"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And leads me to your eyes, where I o'erlook"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Love's stories written in love's richest book."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Wherefore was I to this keen mockery born?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When at your hands did I deserve this scorn?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Is't not enough, is't not enough, young man,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That I did never, no, nor never can,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Deserve a sweet look from Demetrius' eye,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But you must flout my insufficiency?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Good troth, you do me wrong, good sooth, you do,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In such disdainful manner me to woo."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But fare you well: perforce I must confess"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I thought you lord of more true gentleness."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O, that a lady, of one man refused."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Should of another therefore be abused!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "She sees not Hermia. Hermia, sleep thou there:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And never mayst thou come Lysander near!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For as a surfeit of the sweetest things"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The deepest loathing to the stomach brings,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Or as tie heresies that men do leave"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Are hated most of those they did deceive,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So thou, my surfeit and my heresy,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Of all be hated, but the most of me!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And, all my powers, address your love and might"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To honour Helen and to be her knight!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Help me, Lysander, help me! do thy best"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To pluck this crawling serpent from my breast!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ay me, for pity! what a dream was here!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lysander, look how I do quake with fear:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Methought a serpent eat my heart away,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And you sat smiling at his cruel pray."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lysander! what, removed? Lysander! lord!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What, out of hearing? gone? no sound, no word?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Alack, where are you speak, an if you hear;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Speak, of all loves! I swoon almost with fear."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No? then I well perceive you all not nigh"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Either death or you I'll find immediately."]]]],Element "ACT" [Element "TITLE" [PCDATA "ACT III"],Element "SCENE" [Element "TITLE" [PCDATA "SCENE I.  The wood. TITANIA lying asleep."],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Are we all met?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Pat, pat; and here's a marvellous convenient place"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "for our rehearsal. This green plot shall be our"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "stage, this hawthorn-brake our tiring-house; and we"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "will do it in action as we will do it before the duke."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Peter Quince,--"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What sayest thou, bully Bottom?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "There are things in this comedy of Pyramus and"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thisby that will never please. First, Pyramus must"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "draw a sword to kill himself; which the ladies"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "cannot abide. How answer you that?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "SNOUT"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "By'r lakin, a parlous fear."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "STARVELING"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I believe we must leave the killing out, when all is done."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Not a whit: I have a device to make all well."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Write me a prologue; and let the prologue seem to"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "say, we will do no harm with our swords, and that"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Pyramus is not killed indeed; and, for the more"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "better assurance, tell them that I, Pyramus, am not"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Pyramus, but Bottom the weaver: this will put them"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "out of fear."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Well, we will have such a prologue; and it shall be"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "written in eight and six."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No, make it two more; let it be written in eight and eight."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "SNOUT"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Will not the ladies be afeard of the lion?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "STARVELING"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I fear it, I promise you."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Masters, you ought to consider with yourselves: to"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "bring in--God shield us!--a lion among ladies, is a"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "most dreadful thing; for there is not a more fearful"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "wild-fowl than your lion living; and we ought to"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "look to 't."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "SNOUT"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Therefore another prologue must tell he is not a lion."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Nay, you must name his name, and half his face must"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "be seen through the lion's neck: and he himself"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "must speak through, saying thus, or to the same"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "defect,--'Ladies,'--or 'Fair-ladies--I would wish"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You,'--or 'I would request you,'--or 'I would"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "entreat you,--not to fear, not to tremble: my life"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "for yours. If you think I come hither as a lion, it"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "were pity of my life: no I am no such thing; I am a"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "man as other men are;' and there indeed let him name"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "his name, and tell them plainly he is Snug the joiner."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Well it shall be so. But there is two hard things;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "that is, to bring the moonlight into a chamber; for,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "you know, Pyramus and Thisby meet by moonlight."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "SNOUT"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Doth the moon shine that night we play our play?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A calendar, a calendar! look in the almanac; find"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "out moonshine, find out moonshine."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Yes, it doth shine that night."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Why, then may you leave a casement of the great"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "chamber window, where we play, open, and the moon"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "may shine in at the casement."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ay; or else one must come in with a bush of thorns"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "and a lanthorn, and say he comes to disfigure, or to"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "present, the person of Moonshine. Then, there is"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "another thing: we must have a wall in the great"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "chamber; for Pyramus and Thisby says the story, did"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "talk through the chink of a wall."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "SNOUT"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You can never bring in a wall. What say you, Bottom?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Some man or other must present Wall: and let him"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "have some plaster, or some loam, or some rough-cast"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "about him, to signify wall; and let him hold his"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "fingers thus, and through that cranny shall Pyramus"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "and Thisby whisper."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If that may be, then all is well. Come, sit down,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "every mother's son, and rehearse your parts."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Pyramus, you begin: when you have spoken your"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "speech, enter into that brake: and so every one"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "according to his cue."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What hempen home-spuns have we swaggering here,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So near the cradle of the fairy queen?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What, a play toward! I'll be an auditor;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "An actor too, perhaps, if I see cause."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Speak, Pyramus. Thisby, stand forth."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thisby, the flowers of odious savours sweet,--"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Odours, odours."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "--odours savours sweet:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So hath thy breath, my dearest Thisby dear."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But hark, a voice! stay thou but here awhile,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And by and by I will to thee appear."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A stranger Pyramus than e'er played here."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "FLUTE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Must I speak now?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ay, marry, must you; for you must understand he goes"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "but to see a noise that he heard, and is to come again."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "FLUTE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Most radiant Pyramus, most lily-white of hue,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Of colour like the red rose on triumphant brier,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Most brisky juvenal and eke most lovely Jew,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "As true as truest horse that yet would never tire,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I'll meet thee, Pyramus, at Ninny's tomb."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "'Ninus' tomb,' man: why, you must not speak that"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "yet; that you answer to Pyramus: you speak all your"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "part at once, cues and all Pyramus enter: your cue"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "is past; it is, 'never tire.'"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "FLUTE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O,--As true as truest horse, that yet would"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "never tire."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If I were fair, Thisby, I were only thine."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O monstrous! O strange! we are haunted. Pray,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "masters! fly, masters! Help!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I'll follow you, I'll lead you about a round,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Through bog, through bush, through brake, through brier:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Sometime a horse I'll be, sometime a hound,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A hog, a headless bear, sometime a fire;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And neigh, and bark, and grunt, and roar, and burn,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Like horse, hound, hog, bear, fire, at every turn."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Why do they run away? this is a knavery of them to"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "make me afeard."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "SNOUT"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O Bottom, thou art changed! what do I see on thee?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What do you see? you see an asshead of your own, do"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "you?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Bless thee, Bottom! bless thee! thou art"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "translated."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I see their knavery: this is to make an ass of me;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "to fright me, if they could. But I will not stir"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "from this place, do what they can: I will walk up"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "and down here, and I will sing, that they shall hear"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I am not afraid."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The ousel cock so black of hue,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With orange-tawny bill,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The throstle with his note so true,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The wren with little quill,--"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The finch, the sparrow and the lark,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The plain-song cuckoo gray,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Whose note full many a man doth mark,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And dares not answer nay;--"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "for, indeed, who would set his wit to so foolish"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "a bird? who would give a bird the lie, though he cry"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "'cuckoo' never so?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I pray thee, gentle mortal, sing again:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Mine ear is much enamour'd of thy note;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So is mine eye enthralled to thy shape;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And thy fair virtue's force perforce doth move me"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "On the first view to say, to swear, I love thee."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Methinks, mistress, you should have little reason"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "for that: and yet, to say the truth, reason and"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "love keep little company together now-a-days; the"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "more the pity that some honest neighbours will not"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "make them friends. Nay, I can gleek upon occasion."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thou art as wise as thou art beautiful."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Not so, neither: but if I had wit enough to get out"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "of this wood, I have enough to serve mine own turn."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Out of this wood do not desire to go:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thou shalt remain here, whether thou wilt or no."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I am a spirit of no common rate;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The summer still doth tend upon my state;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And I do love thee: therefore, go with me;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I'll give thee fairies to attend on thee,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And they shall fetch thee jewels from the deep,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And sing while thou on pressed flowers dost sleep;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And I will purge thy mortal grossness so"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That thou shalt like an airy spirit go."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Peaseblossom! Cobweb! Moth! and Mustardseed!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PEASEBLOSSOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ready."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "COBWEB"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And I."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "MOTH"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And I."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "MUSTARDSEED"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And I."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "ALL"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Where shall we go?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Be kind and courteous to this gentleman;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hop in his walks and gambol in his eyes;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Feed him with apricocks and dewberries,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With purple grapes, green figs, and mulberries;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The honey-bags steal from the humble-bees,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And for night-tapers crop their waxen thighs"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And light them at the fiery glow-worm's eyes,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To have my love to bed and to arise;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And pluck the wings from Painted butterflies"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To fan the moonbeams from his sleeping eyes:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Nod to him, elves, and do him courtesies."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PEASEBLOSSOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hail, mortal!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "COBWEB"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hail!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "MOTH"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hail!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "MUSTARDSEED"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hail!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I cry your worship's mercy, heartily: I beseech your"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "worship's name."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "COBWEB"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Cobweb."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I shall desire you of more acquaintance, good Master"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Cobweb: if I cut my finger, I shall make bold with"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "you. Your name, honest gentleman?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PEASEBLOSSOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Peaseblossom."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I pray you, commend me to Mistress Squash, your"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "mother, and to Master Peascod, your father. Good"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Master Peaseblossom, I shall desire you of more"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "acquaintance too. Your name, I beseech you, sir?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "MUSTARDSEED"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Mustardseed."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Good Master Mustardseed, I know your patience well:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "that same cowardly, giant-like ox-beef hath"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "devoured many a gentleman of your house: I promise"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "you your kindred had made my eyes water ere now. I"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "desire your more acquaintance, good Master"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Mustardseed."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come, wait upon him; lead him to my bower."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The moon methinks looks with a watery eye;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And when she weeps, weeps every little flower,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lamenting some enforced chastity."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Tie up my love's tongue bring him silently."]]],Element "SCENE" [Element "TITLE" [PCDATA "SCENE II.  Another part of the wood."],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I wonder if Titania be awaked;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Then, what it was that next came in her eye,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Which she must dote on in extremity."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Here comes my messenger."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "How now, mad spirit!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What night-rule now about this haunted grove?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My mistress with a monster is in love."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Near to her close and consecrated bower,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "While she was in her dull and sleeping hour,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A crew of patches, rude mechanicals,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That work for bread upon Athenian stalls,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Were met together to rehearse a play"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Intended for great Theseus' nuptial-day."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The shallowest thick-skin of that barren sort,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Who Pyramus presented, in their sport"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Forsook his scene and enter'd in a brake"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When I did him at this advantage take,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "An ass's nole I fixed on his head:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Anon his Thisbe must be answered,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And forth my mimic comes. When they him spy,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "As wild geese that the creeping fowler eye,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Or russet-pated choughs, many in sort,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Rising and cawing at the gun's report,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Sever themselves and madly sweep the sky,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So, at his sight, away his fellows fly;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And, at our stamp, here o'er and o'er one falls;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "He murder cries and help from Athens calls."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Their sense thus weak, lost with their fears"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "thus strong,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Made senseless things begin to do them wrong;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For briers and thorns at their apparel snatch;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Some sleeves, some hats, from yielders all"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "things catch."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I led them on in this distracted fear,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And left sweet Pyramus translated there:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When in that moment, so it came to pass,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Titania waked and straightway loved an ass."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This falls out better than I could devise."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But hast thou yet latch'd the Athenian's eyes"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With the love-juice, as I did bid thee do?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I took him sleeping,--that is finish'd too,--"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And the Athenian woman by his side:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That, when he waked, of force she must be eyed."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Stand close: this is the same Athenian."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This is the woman, but not this the man."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O, why rebuke you him that loves you so?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lay breath so bitter on your bitter foe."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now I but chide; but I should use thee worse,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For thou, I fear, hast given me cause to curse,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If thou hast slain Lysander in his sleep,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Being o'er shoes in blood, plunge in the deep,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And kill me too."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The sun was not so true unto the day"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "As he to me: would he have stolen away"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "From sleeping Hermia? I'll believe as soon"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This whole earth may be bored and that the moon"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "May through the centre creep and so displease"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Her brother's noontide with Antipodes."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "It cannot be but thou hast murder'd him;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So should a murderer look, so dead, so grim."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So should the murder'd look, and so should I,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Pierced through the heart with your stern cruelty:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Yet you, the murderer, look as bright, as clear,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "As yonder Venus in her glimmering sphere."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What's this to my Lysander? where is he?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ah, good Demetrius, wilt thou give him me?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I had rather give his carcass to my hounds."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Out, dog! out, cur! thou drivest me past the bounds"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Of maiden's patience. Hast thou slain him, then?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Henceforth be never number'd among men!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O, once tell true, tell true, even for my sake!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Durst thou have look'd upon him being awake,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And hast thou kill'd him sleeping? O brave touch!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Could not a worm, an adder, do so much?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "An adder did it; for with doubler tongue"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Than thine, thou serpent, never adder stung."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You spend your passion on a misprised mood:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I am not guilty of Lysander's blood;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Nor is he dead, for aught that I can tell."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I pray thee, tell me then that he is well."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "An if I could, what should I get therefore?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A privilege never to see me more."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And from thy hated presence part I so:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "See me no more, whether he be dead or no."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "There is no following her in this fierce vein:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Here therefore for a while I will remain."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So sorrow's heaviness doth heavier grow"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For debt that bankrupt sleep doth sorrow owe:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Which now in some slight measure it will pay,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If for his tender here I make some stay."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What hast thou done? thou hast mistaken quite"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And laid the love-juice on some true-love's sight:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Of thy misprision must perforce ensue"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Some true love turn'd and not a false turn'd true."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Then fate o'er-rules, that, one man holding troth,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A million fail, confounding oath on oath."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "About the wood go swifter than the wind,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And Helena of Athens look thou find:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "All fancy-sick she is and pale of cheer,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With sighs of love, that costs the fresh blood dear:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "By some illusion see thou bring her here:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I'll charm his eyes against she do appear."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I go, I go; look how I go,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Swifter than arrow from the Tartar's bow."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Flower of this purple dye,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hit with Cupid's archery,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Sink in apple of his eye."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When his love he doth espy,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Let her shine as gloriously"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "As the Venus of the sky."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When thou wakest, if she be by,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Beg of her for remedy."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Captain of our fairy band,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Helena is here at hand;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And the youth, mistook by me,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Pleading for a lover's fee."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Shall we their fond pageant see?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lord, what fools these mortals be!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Stand aside: the noise they make"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Will cause Demetrius to awake."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Then will two at once woo one;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That must needs be sport alone;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And those things do best please me"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That befal preposterously."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Why should you think that I should woo in scorn?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Scorn and derision never come in tears:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Look, when I vow, I weep; and vows so born,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In their nativity all truth appears."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "How can these things in me seem scorn to you,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Bearing the badge of faith, to prove them true?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You do advance your cunning more and more."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When truth kills truth, O devilish-holy fray!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "These vows are Hermia's: will you give her o'er?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Weigh oath with oath, and you will nothing weigh:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Your vows to her and me, put in two scales,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Will even weigh, and both as light as tales."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I had no judgment when to her I swore."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Nor none, in my mind, now you give her o'er."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Demetrius loves her, and he loves not you."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O Helena, goddess, nymph, perfect, divine!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To what, my love, shall I compare thine eyne?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Crystal is muddy. O, how ripe in show"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thy lips, those kissing cherries, tempting grow!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That pure congealed white, high Taurus snow,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Fann'd with the eastern wind, turns to a crow"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When thou hold'st up thy hand: O, let me kiss"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This princess of pure white, this seal of bliss!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O spite! O hell! I see you all are bent"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To set against me for your merriment:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If you we re civil and knew courtesy,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You would not do me thus much injury."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Can you not hate me, as I know you do,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But you must join in souls to mock me too?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If you were men, as men you are in show,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You would not use a gentle lady so;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To vow, and swear, and superpraise my parts,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When I am sure you hate me with your hearts."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You both are rivals, and love Hermia;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And now both rivals, to mock Helena:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A trim exploit, a manly enterprise,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To conjure tears up in a poor maid's eyes"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With your derision! none of noble sort"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Would so offend a virgin, and extort"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A poor soul's patience, all to make you sport."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You are unkind, Demetrius; be not so;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For you love Hermia; this you know I know:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And here, with all good will, with all my heart,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In Hermia's love I yield you up my part;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And yours of Helena to me bequeath,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Whom I do love and will do till my death."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Never did mockers waste more idle breath."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lysander, keep thy Hermia; I will none:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If e'er I loved her, all that love is gone."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My heart to her but as guest-wise sojourn'd,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And now to Helen is it home return'd,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "There to remain."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Helen, it is not so."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Disparage not the faith thou dost not know,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lest, to thy peril, thou aby it dear."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Look, where thy love comes; yonder is thy dear."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Dark night, that from the eye his function takes,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The ear more quick of apprehension makes;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Wherein it doth impair the seeing sense,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "It pays the hearing double recompense."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thou art not by mine eye, Lysander, found;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Mine ear, I thank it, brought me to thy sound"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But why unkindly didst thou leave me so?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Why should he stay, whom love doth press to go?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What love could press Lysander from my side?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lysander's love, that would not let him bide,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Fair Helena, who more engilds the night"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Than all you fiery oes and eyes of light."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Why seek'st thou me? could not this make thee know,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The hate I bear thee made me leave thee so?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You speak not as you think: it cannot be."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lo, she is one of this confederacy!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now I perceive they have conjoin'd all three"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To fashion this false sport, in spite of me."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Injurious Hermia! most ungrateful maid!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Have you conspired, have you with these contrived"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To bait me with this foul derision?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Is all the counsel that we two have shared,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The sisters' vows, the hours that we have spent,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When we have chid the hasty-footed time"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For parting us,--O, is it all forgot?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "All school-days' friendship, childhood innocence?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We, Hermia, like two artificial gods,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Have with our needles created both one flower,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Both on one sampler, sitting on one cushion,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Both warbling of one song, both in one key,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "As if our hands, our sides, voices and minds,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Had been incorporate. So we grow together,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Like to a double cherry, seeming parted,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But yet an union in partition;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Two lovely berries moulded on one stem;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So, with two seeming bodies, but one heart;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Two of the first, like coats in heraldry,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Due but to one and crowned with one crest."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And will you rent our ancient love asunder,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To join with men in scorning your poor friend?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "It is not friendly, 'tis not maidenly:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Our sex, as well as I, may chide you for it,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Though I alone do feel the injury."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I am amazed at your passionate words."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I scorn you not: it seems that you scorn me."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Have you not set Lysander, as in scorn,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To follow me and praise my eyes and face?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And made your other love, Demetrius,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Who even but now did spurn me with his foot,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To call me goddess, nymph, divine and rare,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Precious, celestial? Wherefore speaks he this"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To her he hates? and wherefore doth Lysander"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Deny your love, so rich within his soul,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And tender me, forsooth, affection,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But by your setting on, by your consent?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What thought I be not so in grace as you,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So hung upon with love, so fortunate,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But miserable most, to love unloved?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This you should pity rather than despise."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERNIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I understand not what you mean by this."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ay, do, persever, counterfeit sad looks,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Make mouths upon me when I turn my back;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Wink each at other; hold the sweet jest up:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This sport, well carried, shall be chronicled."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If you have any pity, grace, or manners,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You would not make me such an argument."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But fare ye well: 'tis partly my own fault;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Which death or absence soon shall remedy."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Stay, gentle Helena; hear my excuse:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My love, my life my soul, fair Helena!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O excellent!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Sweet, do not scorn her so."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If she cannot entreat, I can compel."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thou canst compel no more than she entreat:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thy threats have no more strength than her weak prayers."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Helen, I love thee; by my life, I do:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I swear by that which I will lose for thee,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To prove him false that says I love thee not."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I say I love thee more than he can do."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If thou say so, withdraw, and prove it too."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Quick, come!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lysander, whereto tends all this?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Away, you Ethiope!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No, no; he'll"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Seem to break loose; take on as you would follow,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But yet come not: you are a tame man, go!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hang off, thou cat, thou burr! vile thing, let loose,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Or I will shake thee from me like a serpent!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Why are you grown so rude? what change is this?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Sweet love,--"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thy love! out, tawny Tartar, out!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Out, loathed medicine! hated potion, hence!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Do you not jest?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Yes, sooth; and so do you."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Demetrius, I will keep my word with thee."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I would I had your bond, for I perceive"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A weak bond holds you: I'll not trust your word."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What, should I hurt her, strike her, kill her dead?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Although I hate her, I'll not harm her so."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What, can you do me greater harm than hate?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hate me! wherefore? O me! what news, my love!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Am not I Hermia? are not you Lysander?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I am as fair now as I was erewhile."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Since night you loved me; yet since night you left"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "me:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Why, then you left me--O, the gods forbid!--"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In earnest, shall I say?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ay, by my life;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And never did desire to see thee more."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Therefore be out of hope, of question, of doubt;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Be certain, nothing truer; 'tis no jest"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That I do hate thee and love Helena."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O me! you juggler! you canker-blossom!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You thief of love! what, have you come by night"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And stolen my love's heart from him?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Fine, i'faith!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Have you no modesty, no maiden shame,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No touch of bashfulness? What, will you tear"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Impatient answers from my gentle tongue?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Fie, fie! you counterfeit, you puppet, you!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Puppet? why so? ay, that way goes the game."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now I perceive that she hath made compare"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Between our statures; she hath urged her height;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And with her personage, her tall personage,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Her height, forsooth, she hath prevail'd with him."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And are you grown so high in his esteem;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Because I am so dwarfish and so low?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "How low am I, thou painted maypole? speak;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "How low am I? I am not yet so low"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But that my nails can reach unto thine eyes."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I pray you, though you mock me, gentlemen,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Let her not hurt me: I was never curst;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I have no gift at all in shrewishness;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I am a right maid for my cowardice:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Let her not strike me. You perhaps may think,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Because she is something lower than myself,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That I can match her."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lower! hark, again."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Good Hermia, do not be so bitter with me."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I evermore did love you, Hermia,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Did ever keep your counsels, never wrong'd you;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Save that, in love unto Demetrius,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I told him of your stealth unto this wood."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "He follow'd you; for love I follow'd him;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But he hath chid me hence and threaten'd me"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To strike me, spurn me, nay, to kill me too:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And now, so you will let me quiet go,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To Athens will I bear my folly back"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And follow you no further: let me go:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You see how simple and how fond I am."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Why, get you gone: who is't that hinders you?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A foolish heart, that I leave here behind."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What, with Lysander?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With Demetrius."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Be not afraid; she shall not harm thee, Helena."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No, sir, she shall not, though you take her part."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O, when she's angry, she is keen and shrewd!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "She was a vixen when she went to school;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And though she be but little, she is fierce."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "'Little' again! nothing but 'low' and 'little'!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Why will you suffer her to flout me thus?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Let me come to her."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Get you gone, you dwarf;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You minimus, of hindering knot-grass made;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You bead, you acorn."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You are too officious"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In her behalf that scorns your services."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Let her alone: speak not of Helena;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Take not her part; for, if thou dost intend"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Never so little show of love to her,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thou shalt aby it."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now she holds me not;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now follow, if thou darest, to try whose right,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Of thine or mine, is most in Helena."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Follow! nay, I'll go with thee, cheek by jole."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You, mistress, all this coil is 'long of you:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Nay, go not back."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I will not trust you, I,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Nor longer stay in your curst company."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Your hands than mine are quicker for a fray,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My legs are longer though, to run away."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I am amazed, and know not what to say."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This is thy negligence: still thou mistakest,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Or else committ'st thy knaveries wilfully."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Believe me, king of shadows, I mistook."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Did not you tell me I should know the man"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "By the Athenian garment be had on?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And so far blameless proves my enterprise,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That I have 'nointed an Athenian's eyes;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And so far am I glad it so did sort"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "As this their jangling I esteem a sport."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thou see'st these lovers seek a place to fight:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hie therefore, Robin, overcast the night;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The starry welkin cover thou anon"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With drooping fog as black as Acheron,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And lead these testy rivals so astray"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "As one come not within another's way."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Like to Lysander sometime frame thy tongue,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Then stir Demetrius up with bitter wrong;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And sometime rail thou like Demetrius;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And from each other look thou lead them thus,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Till o'er their brows death-counterfeiting sleep"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With leaden legs and batty wings doth creep:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Then crush this herb into Lysander's eye;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Whose liquor hath this virtuous property,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To take from thence all error with his might,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And make his eyeballs roll with wonted sight."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When they next wake, all this derision"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Shall seem a dream and fruitless vision,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And back to Athens shall the lovers wend,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With league whose date till death shall never end."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Whiles I in this affair do thee employ,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I'll to my queen and beg her Indian boy;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And then I will her charmed eye release"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "From monster's view, and all things shall be peace."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My fairy lord, this must be done with haste,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For night's swift dragons cut the clouds full fast,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And yonder shines Aurora's harbinger;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "At whose approach, ghosts, wandering here and there,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Troop home to churchyards: damned spirits all,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That in crossways and floods have burial,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Already to their wormy beds are gone;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For fear lest day should look their shames upon,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "They willfully themselves exile from light"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And must for aye consort with black-brow'd night."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But we are spirits of another sort:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I with the morning's love have oft made sport,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And, like a forester, the groves may tread,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Even till the eastern gate, all fiery-red,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Opening on Neptune with fair blessed beams,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Turns into yellow gold his salt green streams."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But, notwithstanding, haste; make no delay:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We may effect this business yet ere day."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Up and down, up and down,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I will lead them up and down:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I am fear'd in field and town:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Goblin, lead them up and down."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Here comes one."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Where art thou, proud Demetrius? speak thou now."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Here, villain; drawn and ready. Where art thou?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I will be with thee straight."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Follow me, then,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To plainer ground."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lysander! speak again:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thou runaway, thou coward, art thou fled?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Speak! In some bush? Where dost thou hide thy head?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thou coward, art thou bragging to the stars,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Telling the bushes that thou look'st for wars,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And wilt not come? Come, recreant; come, thou child;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I'll whip thee with a rod: he is defiled"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That draws a sword on thee."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Yea, art thou there?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Follow my voice: we'll try no manhood here."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "He goes before me and still dares me on:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When I come where he calls, then he is gone."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The villain is much lighter-heel'd than I:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I follow'd fast, but faster he did fly;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That fallen am I in dark uneven way,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And here will rest me."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come, thou gentle day!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For if but once thou show me thy grey light,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I'll find Demetrius and revenge this spite."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ho, ho, ho! Coward, why comest thou not?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Abide me, if thou darest; for well I wot"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thou runn'st before me, shifting every place,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And darest not stand, nor look me in the face."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Where art thou now?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come hither: I am here."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Nay, then, thou mock'st me. Thou shalt buy this dear,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If ever I thy face by daylight see:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now, go thy way. Faintness constraineth me"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To measure out my length on this cold bed."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "By day's approach look to be visited."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O weary night, O long and tedious night,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Abate thy hour! Shine comforts from the east,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That I may back to Athens by daylight,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "From these that my poor company detest:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And sleep, that sometimes shuts up sorrow's eye,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Steal me awhile from mine own company."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Yet but three? Come one more;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Two of both kinds make up four."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Here she comes, curst and sad:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Cupid is a knavish lad,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thus to make poor females mad."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Never so weary, never so in woe,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Bedabbled with the dew and torn with briers,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I can no further crawl, no further go;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My legs can keep no pace with my desires."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Here will I rest me till the break of day."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Heavens shield Lysander, if they mean a fray!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "On the ground"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Sleep sound:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I'll apply"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To your eye,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Gentle lover, remedy."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When thou wakest,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thou takest"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "True delight"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In the sight"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Of thy former lady's eye:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And the country proverb known,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That every man should take his own,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In your waking shall be shown:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Jack shall have Jill;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Nought shall go ill;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The man shall have his mare again, and all shall be well."]]]],Element "ACT" [Element "TITLE" [PCDATA "ACT IV"],Element "SCENE" [Element "TITLE" [PCDATA "SCENE I.  The same. LYSANDER, DEMETRIUS, HELENA, and HERMIA lying asleep."],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come, sit thee down upon this flowery bed,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "While I thy amiable cheeks do coy,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And stick musk-roses in thy sleek smooth head,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And kiss thy fair large ears, my gentle joy."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Where's Peaseblossom?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PEASEBLOSSOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ready."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Scratch my head Peaseblossom. Where's Mounsieur Cobweb?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "COBWEB"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ready."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Mounsieur Cobweb, good mounsieur, get you your"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "weapons in your hand, and kill me a red-hipped"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "humble-bee on the top of a thistle; and, good"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "mounsieur, bring me the honey-bag. Do not fret"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "yourself too much in the action, mounsieur; and,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "good mounsieur, have a care the honey-bag break not;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I would be loath to have you overflown with a"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "honey-bag, signior. Where's Mounsieur Mustardseed?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "MUSTARDSEED"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ready."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Give me your neaf, Mounsieur Mustardseed. Pray you,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "leave your courtesy, good mounsieur."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "MUSTARDSEED"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What's your Will?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Nothing, good mounsieur, but to help Cavalery Cobweb"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "to scratch. I must to the barber's, monsieur; for"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "methinks I am marvellous hairy about the face; and I"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "am such a tender ass, if my hair do but tickle me,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I must scratch."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What, wilt thou hear some music,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "my sweet love?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I have a reasonable good ear in music. Let's have"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "the tongs and the bones."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Or say, sweet love, what thou desirest to eat."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Truly, a peck of provender: I could munch your good"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "dry oats. Methinks I have a great desire to a bottle"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "of hay: good hay, sweet hay, hath no fellow."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I have a venturous fairy that shall seek"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The squirrel's hoard, and fetch thee new nuts."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I had rather have a handful or two of dried peas."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But, I pray you, let none of your people stir me: I"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "have an exposition of sleep come upon me."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Sleep thou, and I will wind thee in my arms."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Fairies, begone, and be all ways away."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So doth the woodbine the sweet honeysuckle"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Gently entwist; the female ivy so"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Enrings the barky fingers of the elm."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O, how I love thee! how I dote on thee!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Welcome, good Robin."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "See'st thou this sweet sight?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Her dotage now I do begin to pity:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For, meeting her of late behind the wood,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Seeking sweet favours from this hateful fool,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I did upbraid her and fall out with her;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For she his hairy temples then had rounded"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With a coronet of fresh and fragrant flowers;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And that same dew, which sometime on the buds"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Was wont to swell like round and orient pearls,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Stood now within the pretty flowerets' eyes"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Like tears that did their own disgrace bewail."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When I had at my pleasure taunted her"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And she in mild terms begg'd my patience,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I then did ask of her her changeling child;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Which straight she gave me, and her fairy sent"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To bear him to my bower in fairy land."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And now I have the boy, I will undo"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This hateful imperfection of her eyes:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And, gentle Puck, take this transformed scalp"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "From off the head of this Athenian swain;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That, he awaking when the other do,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "May all to Athens back again repair"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And think no more of this night's accidents"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But as the fierce vexation of a dream."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But first I will release the fairy queen."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Be as thou wast wont to be;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "See as thou wast wont to see:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Dian's bud o'er Cupid's flower"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hath such force and blessed power."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now, my Titania; wake you, my sweet queen."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My Oberon! what visions have I seen!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Methought I was enamour'd of an ass."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "There lies your love."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "How came these things to pass?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O, how mine eyes do loathe his visage now!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Silence awhile. Robin, take off this head."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Titania, music call; and strike more dead"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Than common sleep of all these five the sense."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Music, ho! music, such as charmeth sleep!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now, when thou wakest, with thine"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "own fool's eyes peep."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Sound, music! Come, my queen, take hands with me,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And rock the ground whereon these sleepers be."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now thou and I are new in amity,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And will to-morrow midnight solemnly"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Dance in Duke Theseus' house triumphantly,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And bless it to all fair prosperity:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "There shall the pairs of faithful lovers be"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Wedded, with Theseus, all in jollity."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Fairy king, attend, and mark:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I do hear the morning lark."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Then, my queen, in silence sad,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Trip we after the night's shade:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We the globe can compass soon,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Swifter than the wandering moon."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come, my lord, and in our flight"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Tell me how it came this night"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That I sleeping here was found"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With these mortals on the ground."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Go, one of you, find out the forester;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For now our observation is perform'd;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And since we have the vaward of the day,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My love shall hear the music of my hounds."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Uncouple in the western valley; let them go:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Dispatch, I say, and find the forester."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We will, fair queen, up to the mountain's top,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And mark the musical confusion"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Of hounds and echo in conjunction."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HIPPOLYTA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I was with Hercules and Cadmus once,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When in a wood of Crete they bay'd the bear"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With hounds of Sparta: never did I hear"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Such gallant chiding: for, besides the groves,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The skies, the fountains, every region near"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Seem'd all one mutual cry: I never heard"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So musical a discord, such sweet thunder."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My hounds are bred out of the Spartan kind,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So flew'd, so sanded, and their heads are hung"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With ears that sweep away the morning dew;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Crook-knee'd, and dew-lapp'd like Thessalian bulls;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Slow in pursuit, but match'd in mouth like bells,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Each under each. A cry more tuneable"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Was never holla'd to, nor cheer'd with horn,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In Crete, in Sparta, nor in Thessaly:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Judge when you hear. But, soft! what nymphs are these?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "EGEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My lord, this is my daughter here asleep;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And this, Lysander; this Demetrius is;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This Helena, old Nedar's Helena:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I wonder of their being here together."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No doubt they rose up early to observe"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The rite of May, and hearing our intent,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Came here in grace our solemnity."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But speak, Egeus; is not this the day"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That Hermia should give answer of her choice?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "EGEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "It is, my lord."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Go, bid the huntsmen wake them with their horns."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Good morrow, friends. Saint Valentine is past:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Begin these wood-birds but to couple now?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Pardon, my lord."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I pray you all, stand up."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I know you two are rival enemies:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "How comes this gentle concord in the world,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That hatred is so far from jealousy,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To sleep by hate, and fear no enmity?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My lord, I shall reply amazedly,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Half sleep, half waking: but as yet, I swear,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I cannot truly say how I came here;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But, as I think,--for truly would I speak,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And now do I bethink me, so it is,--"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I came with Hermia hither: our intent"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Was to be gone from Athens, where we might,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Without the peril of the Athenian law."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "EGEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Enough, enough, my lord; you have enough:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I beg the law, the law, upon his head."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "They would have stolen away; they would, Demetrius,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thereby to have defeated you and me,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You of your wife and me of my consent,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Of my consent that she should be your wife."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My lord, fair Helen told me of their stealth,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Of this their purpose hither to this wood;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And I in fury hither follow'd them,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Fair Helena in fancy following me."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But, my good lord, I wot not by what power,--"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But by some power it is,--my love to Hermia,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Melted as the snow, seems to me now"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "As the remembrance of an idle gaud"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Which in my childhood I did dote upon;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And all the faith, the virtue of my heart,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The object and the pleasure of mine eye,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Is only Helena. To her, my lord,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Was I betroth'd ere I saw Hermia:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But, like in sickness, did I loathe this food;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But, as in health, come to my natural taste,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now I do wish it, love it, long for it,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And will for evermore be true to it."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Fair lovers, you are fortunately met:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Of this discourse we more will hear anon."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Egeus, I will overbear your will;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For in the temple by and by with us"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "These couples shall eternally be knit:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And, for the morning now is something worn,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Our purposed hunting shall be set aside."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Away with us to Athens; three and three,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We'll hold a feast in great solemnity."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come, Hippolyta."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "These things seem small and undistinguishable,"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Methinks I see these things with parted eye,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When every thing seems double."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So methinks:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And I have found Demetrius like a jewel,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Mine own, and not mine own."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Are you sure"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That we are awake? It seems to me"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That yet we sleep, we dream. Do not you think"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The duke was here, and bid us follow him?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HERMIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Yea; and my father."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HELENA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And Hippolyta."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And he did bid us follow to the temple."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Why, then, we are awake: let's follow him"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And by the way let us recount our dreams."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When my cue comes, call me, and I will"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "answer: my next is, 'Most fair Pyramus.' Heigh-ho!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Peter Quince! Flute, the bellows-mender! Snout,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "the tinker! Starveling! God's my life, stolen"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "hence, and left me asleep! I have had a most rare"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "vision. I have had a dream, past the wit of man to"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "say what dream it was: man is but an ass, if he go"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "about to expound this dream. Methought I was--there"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "is no man can tell what. Methought I was,--and"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "methought I had,--but man is but a patched fool, if"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "he will offer to say what methought I had. The eye"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "of man hath not heard, the ear of man hath not"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "seen, man's hand is not able to taste, his tongue"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "to conceive, nor his heart to report, what my dream"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "was. I will get Peter Quince to write a ballad of"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "this dream: it shall be called Bottom's Dream,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "because it hath no bottom; and I will sing it in the"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "latter end of a play, before the duke:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "peradventure, to make it the more gracious, I shall"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "sing it at her death."]]],Element "SCENE" [Element "TITLE" [PCDATA "SCENE II.  Athens. QUINCE'S house."],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Have you sent to Bottom's house? is he come home yet?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "STARVELING"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "He cannot be heard of. Out of doubt he is"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "transported."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "FLUTE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If he come not, then the play is marred: it goes"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "not forward, doth it?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "It is not possible: you have not a man in all"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Athens able to discharge Pyramus but he."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "FLUTE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No, he hath simply the best wit of any handicraft"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "man in Athens."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Yea and the best person too; and he is a very"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "paramour for a sweet voice."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "FLUTE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You must say 'paragon:' a paramour is, God bless us,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "a thing of naught."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "SNUG"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Masters, the duke is coming from the temple, and"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "there is two or three lords and ladies more married:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "if our sport had gone forward, we had all been made"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "men."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "FLUTE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O sweet bully Bottom! Thus hath he lost sixpence a"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "day during his life; he could not have 'scaped"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "sixpence a day: an the duke had not given him"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "sixpence a day for playing Pyramus, I'll be hanged;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "he would have deserved it: sixpence a day in"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Pyramus, or nothing."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Where are these lads? where are these hearts?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Bottom! O most courageous day! O most happy hour!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Masters, I am to discourse wonders: but ask me not"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "what; for if I tell you, I am no true Athenian. I"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "will tell you every thing, right as it fell out."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "QUINCE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Let us hear, sweet Bottom."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Not a word of me. All that I will tell you is, that"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "the duke hath dined. Get your apparel together,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "good strings to your beards, new ribbons to your"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "pumps; meet presently at the palace; every man look"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "o'er his part; for the short and the long is, our"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "play is preferred. In any case, let Thisby have"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "clean linen; and let not him that plays the lion"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "pair his nails, for they shall hang out for the"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "lion's claws. And, most dear actors, eat no onions"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "nor garlic, for we are to utter sweet breath; and I"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "do not doubt but to hear them say, it is a sweet"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "comedy. No more words: away! go, away!"]]]],Element "ACT" [Element "TITLE" [PCDATA "ACT V"],Element "SCENE" [Element "TITLE" [PCDATA "SCENE I.  Athens. The palace of THESEUS."],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HIPPOLYTA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "'Tis strange my Theseus, that these"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "lovers speak of."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "More strange than true: I never may believe"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "These antique fables, nor these fairy toys."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lovers and madmen have such seething brains,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Such shaping fantasies, that apprehend"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "More than cool reason ever comprehends."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The lunatic, the lover and the poet"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Are of imagination all compact:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "One sees more devils than vast hell can hold,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That is, the madman: the lover, all as frantic,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Sees Helen's beauty in a brow of Egypt:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The poet's eye, in fine frenzy rolling,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Doth glance from heaven to earth, from earth to heaven;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And as imagination bodies forth"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The forms of things unknown, the poet's pen"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Turns them to shapes and gives to airy nothing"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A local habitation and a name."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Such tricks hath strong imagination,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That if it would but apprehend some joy,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "It comprehends some bringer of that joy;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Or in the night, imagining some fear,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "How easy is a bush supposed a bear!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HIPPOLYTA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But all the story of the night told over,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And all their minds transfigured so together,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "More witnesseth than fancy's images"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And grows to something of great constancy;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But, howsoever, strange and admirable."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Here come the lovers, full of joy and mirth."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Joy, gentle friends! joy and fresh days of love"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Accompany your hearts!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "More than to us"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Wait in your royal walks, your board, your bed!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come now; what masques, what dances shall we have,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To wear away this long age of three hours"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Between our after-supper and bed-time?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Where is our usual manager of mirth?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What revels are in hand? Is there no play,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To ease the anguish of a torturing hour?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Call Philostrate."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PHILOSTRATE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Here, mighty Theseus."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Say, what abridgement have you for this evening?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What masque? what music? How shall we beguile"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The lazy time, if not with some delight?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PHILOSTRATE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "There is a brief how many sports are ripe:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Make choice of which your highness will see first."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "'The battle with the Centaurs, to be sung"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "By an Athenian eunuch to the harp.'"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We'll none of that: that have I told my love,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In glory of my kinsman Hercules."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "'The riot of the tipsy Bacchanals,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Tearing the Thracian singer in their rage.'"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That is an old device; and it was play'd"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When I from Thebes came last a conqueror."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "'The thrice three Muses mourning for the death"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Of Learning, late deceased in beggary.'"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That is some satire, keen and critical,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Not sorting with a nuptial ceremony."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "'A tedious brief scene of young Pyramus"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And his love Thisbe; very tragical mirth.'"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Merry and tragical! tedious and brief!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That is, hot ice and wondrous strange snow."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "How shall we find the concord of this discord?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PHILOSTRATE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A play there is, my lord, some ten words long,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Which is as brief as I have known a play;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But by ten words, my lord, it is too long,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Which makes it tedious; for in all the play"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "There is not one word apt, one player fitted:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And tragical, my noble lord, it is;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For Pyramus therein doth kill himself."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Which, when I saw rehearsed, I must confess,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Made mine eyes water; but more merry tears"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The passion of loud laughter never shed."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What are they that do play it?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PHILOSTRATE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hard-handed men that work in Athens here,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Which never labour'd in their minds till now,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And now have toil'd their unbreathed memories"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With this same play, against your nuptial."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And we will hear it."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PHILOSTRATE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No, my noble lord;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "It is not for you: I have heard it over,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And it is nothing, nothing in the world;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Unless you can find sport in their intents,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Extremely stretch'd and conn'd with cruel pain,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To do you service."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I will hear that play;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For never anything can be amiss,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When simpleness and duty tender it."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Go, bring them in: and take your places, ladies."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HIPPOLYTA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I love not to see wretchedness o'er charged"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And duty in his service perishing."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Why, gentle sweet, you shall see no such thing."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HIPPOLYTA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "He says they can do nothing in this kind."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The kinder we, to give them thanks for nothing."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Our sport shall be to take what they mistake:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And what poor duty cannot do, noble respect"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Takes it in might, not merit."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Where I have come, great clerks have purposed"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To greet me with premeditated welcomes;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Where I have seen them shiver and look pale,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Make periods in the midst of sentences,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Throttle their practised accent in their fears"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And in conclusion dumbly have broke off,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Not paying me a welcome. Trust me, sweet,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Out of this silence yet I pick'd a welcome;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And in the modesty of fearful duty"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I read as much as from the rattling tongue"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Of saucy and audacious eloquence."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Love, therefore, and tongue-tied simplicity"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In least speak most, to my capacity."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PHILOSTRATE"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So please your grace, the Prologue is address'd."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Let him approach."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Prologue"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If we offend, it is with our good will."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That you should think, we come not to offend,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But with good will. To show our simple skill,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That is the true beginning of our end."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Consider then we come but in despite."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We do not come as minding to contest you,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Our true intent is. All for your delight"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We are not here. That you should here repent you,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The actors are at hand and by their show"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You shall know all that you are like to know."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This fellow doth not stand upon points."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "He hath rid his prologue like a rough colt; he knows"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "not the stop. A good moral, my lord: it is not"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "enough to speak, but to speak true."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HIPPOLYTA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Indeed he hath played on his prologue like a child"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "on a recorder; a sound, but not in government."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "His speech, was like a tangled chain; nothing"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "impaired, but all disordered. Who is next?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Prologue"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Gentles, perchance you wonder at this show;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But wonder on, till truth make all things plain."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This man is Pyramus, if you would know;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This beauteous lady Thisby is certain."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This man, with lime and rough-cast, doth present"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Wall, that vile Wall which did these lovers sunder;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And through Wall's chink, poor souls, they are content"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To whisper. At the which let no man wonder."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This man, with lanthorn, dog, and bush of thorn,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Presenteth Moonshine; for, if you will know,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "By moonshine did these lovers think no scorn"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To meet at Ninus' tomb, there, there to woo."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This grisly beast, which Lion hight by name,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The trusty Thisby, coming first by night,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Did scare away, or rather did affright;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And, as she fled, her mantle she did fall,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Which Lion vile with bloody mouth did stain."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Anon comes Pyramus, sweet youth and tall,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And finds his trusty Thisby's mantle slain:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Whereat, with blade, with bloody blameful blade,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "He bravely broach'd is boiling bloody breast;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And Thisby, tarrying in mulberry shade,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "His dagger drew, and died. For all the rest,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Let Lion, Moonshine, Wall, and lovers twain"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "At large discourse, while here they do remain."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I wonder if the lion be to speak."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No wonder, my lord: one lion may, when many asses do."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Wall"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In this same interlude it doth befall"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That I, one Snout by name, present a wall;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And such a wall, as I would have you think,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That had in it a crannied hole or chink,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Through which the lovers, Pyramus and Thisby,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Did whisper often very secretly."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This loam, this rough-cast and this stone doth show"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That I am that same wall; the truth is so:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And this the cranny is, right and sinister,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Through which the fearful lovers are to whisper."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Would you desire lime and hair to speak better?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "It is the wittiest partition that ever I heard"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "discourse, my lord."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Pyramus draws near the wall: silence!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Pyramus"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O grim-look'd night! O night with hue so black!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O night, which ever art when day is not!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O night, O night! alack, alack, alack,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I fear my Thisby's promise is forgot!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And thou, O wall, O sweet, O lovely wall,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That stand'st between her father's ground and mine!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thou wall, O wall, O sweet and lovely wall,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Show me thy chink, to blink through with mine eyne!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thanks, courteous wall: Jove shield thee well for this!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But what see I? No Thisby do I see."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O wicked wall, through whom I see no bliss!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Cursed be thy stones for thus deceiving me!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The wall, methinks, being sensible, should curse again."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Pyramus"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No, in truth, sir, he should not. 'Deceiving me'"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "is Thisby's cue: she is to enter now, and I am to"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "spy her through the wall. You shall see, it will"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "fall pat as I told you. Yonder she comes."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Thisbe"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O wall, full often hast thou heard my moans,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For parting my fair Pyramus and me!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My cherry lips have often kiss'd thy stones,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thy stones with lime and hair knit up in thee."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Pyramus"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I see a voice: now will I to the chink,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To spy an I can hear my Thisby's face. Thisby!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Thisbe"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My love thou art, my love I think."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Pyramus"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Think what thou wilt, I am thy lover's grace;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And, like Limander, am I trusty still."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Thisbe"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And I like Helen, till the Fates me kill."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Pyramus"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Not Shafalus to Procrus was so true."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Thisbe"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "As Shafalus to Procrus, I to you."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Pyramus"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O kiss me through the hole of this vile wall!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Thisbe"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I kiss the wall's hole, not your lips at all."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Pyramus"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Wilt thou at Ninny's tomb meet me straightway?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Thisbe"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "'Tide life, 'tide death, I come without delay."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Wall"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thus have I, Wall, my part discharged so;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And, being done, thus Wall away doth go."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now is the mural down between the two neighbours."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No remedy, my lord, when walls are so wilful to hear"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "without warning."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HIPPOLYTA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This is the silliest stuff that ever I heard."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The best in this kind are but shadows; and the worst"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "are no worse, if imagination amend them."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HIPPOLYTA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "It must be your imagination then, and not theirs."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If we imagine no worse of them than they of"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "themselves, they may pass for excellent men. Here"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "come two noble beasts in, a man and a lion."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Lion"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "You, ladies, you, whose gentle hearts do fear"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The smallest monstrous mouse that creeps on floor,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "May now perchance both quake and tremble here,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "When lion rough in wildest rage doth roar."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Then know that I, one Snug the joiner, am"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A lion-fell, nor else no lion's dam;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For, if I should as lion come in strife"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Into this place, 'twere pity on my life."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A very gentle beast, of a good conscience."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The very best at a beast, my lord, that e'er I saw."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This lion is a very fox for his valour."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "True; and a goose for his discretion."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Not so, my lord; for his valour cannot carry his"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "discretion; and the fox carries the goose."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "His discretion, I am sure, cannot carry his valour;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "for the goose carries not the fox. It is well:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "leave it to his discretion, and let us listen to the moon."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Moonshine"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This lanthorn doth the horned moon present;--"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "He should have worn the horns on his head."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "He is no crescent, and his horns are"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "invisible within the circumference."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Moonshine"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This lanthorn doth the horned moon present;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Myself the man i' the moon do seem to be."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This is the greatest error of all the rest: the man"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "should be put into the lanthorn. How is it else the"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "man i' the moon?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "He dares not come there for the candle; for, you"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "see, it is already in snuff."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HIPPOLYTA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I am aweary of this moon: would he would change!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "It appears, by his small light of discretion, that"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "he is in the wane; but yet, in courtesy, in all"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "reason, we must stay the time."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Proceed, Moon."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Moonshine"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "All that I have to say, is, to tell you that the"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "lanthorn is the moon; I, the man in the moon; this"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "thorn-bush, my thorn-bush; and this dog, my dog."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Why, all these should be in the lanthorn; for all"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "these are in the moon. But, silence! here comes Thisbe."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Thisbe"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This is old Ninny's tomb. Where is my love?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Lion"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Oh--"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Well roared, Lion."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Well run, Thisbe."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HIPPOLYTA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Well shone, Moon. Truly, the moon shines with a"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "good grace."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Well moused, Lion."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And so the lion vanished."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And then came Pyramus."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Pyramus"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Sweet Moon, I thank thee for thy sunny beams;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I thank thee, Moon, for shining now so bright;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "For, by thy gracious, golden, glittering gleams,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I trust to take of truest Thisby sight."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But stay, O spite!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "But mark, poor knight,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What dreadful dole is here!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Eyes, do you see?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "How can it be?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O dainty duck! O dear!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thy mantle good,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What, stain'd with blood!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Approach, ye Furies fell!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O Fates, come, come,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Cut thread and thrum;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Quail, crush, conclude, and quell!"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This passion, and the death of a dear friend, would"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "go near to make a man look sad."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HIPPOLYTA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Beshrew my heart, but I pity the man."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Pyramus"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O wherefore, Nature, didst thou lions frame?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Since lion vile hath here deflower'd my dear:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Which is--no, no--which was the fairest dame"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That lived, that loved, that liked, that look'd"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "with cheer."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come, tears, confound;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Out, sword, and wound"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The pap of Pyramus;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ay, that left pap,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Where heart doth hop:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thus die I, thus, thus, thus."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now am I dead,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now am I fled;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "My soul is in the sky:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Tongue, lose thy light;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Moon take thy flight:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now die, die, die, die, die."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No die, but an ace, for him; for he is but one."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Less than an ace, man; for he is dead; he is nothing."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With the help of a surgeon he might yet recover, and"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "prove an ass."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HIPPOLYTA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "How chance Moonshine is gone before Thisbe comes"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "back and finds her lover?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "She will find him by starlight. Here she comes; and"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "her passion ends the play."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "HIPPOLYTA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Methinks she should not use a long one for such a"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Pyramus: I hope she will be brief."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A mote will turn the balance, which Pyramus, which"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thisbe, is the better; he for a man, God warrant us;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "she for a woman, God bless us."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "LYSANDER"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "She hath spied him already with those sweet eyes."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And thus she means, videlicet:--"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "Thisbe"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Asleep, my love?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "What, dead, my dove?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O Pyramus, arise!"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Speak, speak. Quite dumb?"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Dead, dead? A tomb"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Must cover thy sweet eyes."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "These My lips,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This cherry nose,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "These yellow cowslip cheeks,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Are gone, are gone:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lovers, make moan:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "His eyes were green as leeks."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "O Sisters Three,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come, come to me,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With hands as pale as milk;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lay them in gore,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Since you have shore"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With shears his thread of silk."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Tongue, not a word:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come, trusty sword;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Come, blade, my breast imbrue:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And, farewell, friends;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Thus Thisby ends:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Adieu, adieu, adieu."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Moonshine and Lion are left to bury the dead."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "DEMETRIUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ay, and Wall too."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "BOTTOM"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No assure you; the wall is down that"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "parted their fathers. Will it please you to see the"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "epilogue, or to hear a Bergomask dance between two"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "of our company?"]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "THESEUS"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No epilogue, I pray you; for your play needs no"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "excuse. Never excuse; for when the players are all"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "dead, there needs none to be blamed. Marry, if he"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "that writ it had played Pyramus and hanged himself"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "in Thisbe's garter, it would have been a fine"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "tragedy: and so it is, truly; and very notably"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "discharged. But come, your Bergomask: let your"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "epilogue alone."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The iron tongue of midnight hath told twelve:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Lovers, to bed; 'tis almost fairy time."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I fear we shall out-sleep the coming morn"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "As much as we this night have overwatch'd."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "This palpable-gross play hath well beguiled"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "The heavy gait of night. Sweet friends, to bed."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "A fortnight hold we this solemnity,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In nightly revels and new jollity."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now the hungry lion roars,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And the wolf behowls the moon;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Whilst the heavy ploughman snores,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "All with weary task fordone."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now the wasted brands do glow,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Whilst the screech-owl, screeching loud,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Puts the wretch that lies in woe"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In remembrance of a shroud."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now it is the time of night"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That the graves all gaping wide,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Every one lets forth his sprite,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "In the church-way paths to glide:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And we fairies, that do run"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "By the triple Hecate's team,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "From the presence of the sun,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Following darkness like a dream,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now are frolic: not a mouse"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Shall disturb this hallow'd house:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "I am sent with broom before,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To sweep the dust behind the door."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Through the house give gathering light,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "By the dead and drowsy fire:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Every elf and fairy sprite"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hop as light as bird from brier;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And this ditty, after me,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Sing, and dance it trippingly."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "TITANIA"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "First, rehearse your song by rote"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To each word a warbling note:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Hand in hand, with fairy grace,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Will we sing, and bless this place."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "OBERON"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now, until the break of day,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Through this house each fairy stray."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "To the best bride-bed will we,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Which by us shall blessed be;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And the issue there create"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ever shall be fortunate."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So shall all the couples three"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ever true in loving be;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And the blots of Nature's hand"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Shall not in their issue stand;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Never mole, hare lip, nor scar,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Nor mark prodigious, such as are"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Despised in nativity,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Shall upon their children be."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "With this field-dew consecrate,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Every fairy take his gait;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And each several chamber bless,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Through this palace, with sweet peace;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And the owner of it blest"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Ever shall in safety rest."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Trip away; make no stay;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Meet me all by break of day."]],Element "SPEECH" [Element "SPEAKER" [PCDATA "PUCK"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If we shadows have offended,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Think but this, and all is mended,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "That you have but slumber'd here"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "While these visions did appear."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And this weak and idle theme,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "No more yielding but a dream,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Gentles, do not reprehend:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "if you pardon, we will mend:"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And, as I am an honest Puck,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "If we have unearned luck"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Now to 'scape the serpent's tongue,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "We will make amends ere long;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Else the Puck a liar call;"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "So, good night unto you all."],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "Give me your hands, if we be friends,"],Element "LINE" [PCDATA "And Robin shall restore amends."]]]]]